  "prompt": "Does the 112 emergency number work in the USA?",
  "response": "No, the emergency number 112 does not work universally in the USA. In the United States, the primary emergency phone number is 911. However, it is worth noting that some areas or devices may support 112 as a secondary option, particularly in regions close to the U.S. border or on mobile networks that have been set up to recognize it. For emergency assistance in the U.S., it is recommended to use 911.",
